post_text:
The Illinois Department of Public Health is currently sponsoring community-based COVID-19 testing sites throughout Illinois. Testing is provided at no cost to individuals, no appointment or medical referral is needed, and insurance is not required. Testing is available for all ages; however, parents or guardians must be present and able to provide consent for those under the age of 18.

The following community-based testing site (CBTS) in your area is now open for free testing:
• South Suburban College
15800 State Street
8:00 – 4:00pm; 7 days a week

post_text: Taft is hosting a fundraiser on August 26, 2020 at Chipotle in South Holland from 4pm-8pm. Please consider stopping in for dinner to support Taft! You don’t need the printout, just tell the cashier that you are supporting Taft. Due to Covid-19, Chipotle is accepting online orders for the fundraising. You can order online and pick it up at 559 E 162nd St in South Holland on your way home using the promo code – GE2BPAQ. Thank you for your support! We really appreciate it!

The City of Harvey
August 14 at 3:09 PM ·

Harvey residents. We are continuing to hand out free food throughout the day until 8:00 pm at Bryant School, 14730 Main St. Tell a neighbor. Help a neighbor. Please notify the city of Harvey at 708-210-5300 between the hours of 9a and 5p if you know of anyone that requires food or health care assistance. If you know someone who is unable to call for assistance or is disabled, please call on their behalf. If you are presently in an emergency or life threatening situation, please call 911 immediately.

Apply August 10th IHDA.Org

Per the Governor, starting August 10th, renters will be able to apply for grants of up to $5,000 each to cover rent. Starting Aug. 24th, Homeowners can apply for up to $15,000 mortgage-relief grants from the Illinois Housing Development Authority. The $150 million Emergency Rental Assistance Program is expected to help about 30,000 people in the state. Go here:

IHDA.org

Have an amazing day!

Imagine the fun, imagine the friendships, imagine the connections!

Anyone living with diabetes between the ages 5-17 is invited to join us this summer for one, or both, of our four-week in-home American Diabetes Association Imagine Camp sessions filled with weekly themes, activities, cabin meetings and more!

Session 1: June 8- July 3
Session 2: July 13-August 7

Register for FREE at: diabetes.org/imaginecamp

#ConnectedforLife #BecauseofADACamps #ADAImagineCamp

post_text:
If you have less than 10 minutes to spare during this “Shelter in Place” time, please complete your 2020census.gov . As you know, census data affects our community: schools, parks, grocery stores, banks, etc.

We need all those things and more to help keep our community great!

I received a form to be completed and mail to the Census Department and a letter stating I could do it on-line. I completed it on-line.

Who’s with me? It took me less than 8 minutes to complete the 2020 Census.

So, let’s get counted.
text:
If you have less than 10 minutes to spare during this “Shelter in Place” time, please complete your 2020census.gov . As you know, census data affects our community: schools, parks, grocery stores, banks, etc.

We need all those things and more to help keep our community great!

I received a form to be completed and mail to the Census Department and a letter stating I could do it on-line. I completed it on-line.

Who’s with me? It took me less than 8 minutes to complete the 2020 Census.

So, let’s get counted.

post_text:
On Friday, the Governor issued a stay-at-home order for the State of Illinois until April 7. This means everyone in the state is required to stay at home as much as possible. All of our schools will continue to be closed until at least April 8, 2020.

Our schools will continue to provide lunches for children aged 18 and under on each week day. Eisenhower Madison and Coolidge will now do lunch distribution from 10 AM until 12 PM each weekday. Taft will continue to do lunch distribution from 11 AM until 12:30 PM each weekday.

We will also continue to provide e-Learning and Home Learning activities for students. Please visit our website at www.shsd151.org

text:
On Friday, the Governor issued a stay-at-home order for the State of Illinois until April 7. This means everyone in the state is required to stay at home as much as possible. All of our schools will continue to be closed until at least April 8, 2020.

Our schools will continue to provide lunches for children aged 18 and under on each week day. Eisenhower Madison and Coolidge will now do lunch distribution from 10 AM until 12 PM each weekday. Taft will continue to do lunch distribution from 11 AM until 12:30 PM each weekday.

We will also continue to provide e-Learning and Home Learning activities for students. Please visit our website at www.shsd151.org

All South Holland School District 151 schools will be closed tomorrow, Monday, March 16.

Taft, Eisenhower, Madison and Coolidge will be closed Monday due to concerns about the coronavirus. All schools and offices will stay closed until after Spring Break.

All schools will provide e-Learning or Home Learning activities for students while schools are closed. Please check your email and the district website for more information.

Reading is fun and evidently profitable. 🤣 The children and parents won prizes, which included gym shoes made a former Thornridge student; a 32 in television donated by the Phoenix Park District; coats donated by Rep. Will Davis; board games; 3 bikes; much more and of course EVERY child left with a book to enjoy!

The Phoenix Public Library did a phenomenal job. What a way to celebrate reading! ❤
